2212 Sir Shop-a-Lot 2020-01-27 Fire TV Stick True 5.0 Another one of life-changing and unique Amazon products. Definitively a Must Have! Discount:\nBought it for a discount at 3199INR. It's available on this price at almost all the amazon sales, so better to google upcoming sales and then purchase.\nUses:\nI use it for internet surfing, video streaming, music, games, screen-mirroring (from phone, tablet, PC), and live TV (through JioTV). No point in paying for Tata Sky and the likes since you can install JioTV and enjoy live television for free.\nAdditional features:\ni) Remote:\nPremium build, ergonomic design, and flawless voice recognition. All of the buttons are well spaced and tactile to press. The voice search works most of the time, but manual typing requires selecting letters one by one from the on-screen keyboard using remote keys, so that becomes a hassle sometimes. The remote has buttons for skipping forward and backward in the video, so navigating becomes really easy.\nii) Bluetooth Connectivity:\nThere's also the option to pair the Firestick with bluetooth supporting devices such as mouse, keyboard, earphones, etc. Typing with a keyboard is a lot easier than using the on-screen keyboard, and there's an app called 'Mouse Toggle' which enables a mouse pointer which can be controlled by a bluetooth mouse for easier surfing in some apps. Bluetooth earphones work perfectly too, with no loss in quality.\niii) Internet surfing\nIt has an inbuilt browser. There is also a way to install FireFox browser in it as well. Coupled with a keyboard and a mouse, accessing internet becomes as easy as it is on PC.\niv) Universal search for all the streaming apps\nJust press the voice search button, say the name of the movie or series, and it will search through all of your apps to find where it's hosted. Really convenient to have everything in one place.\nv) Other awesome features\nThere's a button for quickly changing audio and subtitle language on the remote itself.\nWhatever you play gets resumed from where you've left it.\nRecently played videos are shown at the home-screen.\nAutomatically connects to the saved networks.\nPrivacy friendly, with options to opt-out of user experience programme.\nMany more little conveniences, making streaming a pleasurable experience.\nOnly suggestion I'd make is that they should make their UI more cleaner, especially at the pause screen of the videos.\nFinal words:\nSo far, it has been a complete positive experience. I've bought two of them and replaced my Tata Sky subsciptions. If you have a decent internet connection with unlimited bandwidth, then FireStick is for you.
